Utterance.UttText: The bed six, Lisa Kerr, 62 yrs old under Dr Laine, came in with apoplexy(cerebral haemorrhage), she just came in 3 hrs ago and have taken her obs and it is all normal.
She is on neuro obs aswell and scoring a score of 15 on GCS.
no weakness on both arms and legs.

Candidate.CandidatePreferred: Entire lower leg, from knee to ankle

Utterance.UttText: She had CT of the brain which showed cerebral haemorrhage and on emergency list for brain surgery today.
She was kept fasting from ED.
We are still waiting for the husband to arrive to give consent because he's got the power of attorney.
She is confused and wont be able to sign the consent.
She is on a gown and her preop check list have been done.
